chunks.text: ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## VA (HTM) WORK ORDER CLERK TRAINING ## VA Work Order Clerk Role in Maximo In Maximo, the VA Work Order Clerk role reviews Service Requests and creates, assigns ownership, and updates Work Order statuses. NOTE: The VA Work Order Clerk role is often referred to as the HTM Work Order Clerk , and the terms are used interchangeably. As a matter of practicality, documentation for the VA/HTM WO Clerk is stored within Healthcare Technology Maintenance (HTM) Functional Community on the SOARD Maximo Training Page. ## Available Training Resources User Guides, Job Aids and Quick Reference Documents are available on the EAWM Maximo Training Page to help users learn their role and responsibilities in Maximo at their own pace and in a mode that best fits their learning style. - · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process

- · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus on key issues, highlighting essential steps. These are found in the 'User Documentation' section of the Training page. - · Quick Reference Documents (QRDs) include step-by-step work instructions, in simplest terms. Unlike Job Aids and User Guides, QRDs normally do not include screen captures. These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. - · Video Demonstrations allow playback of recorded sessions narrated by Instructors, walking through the ste

These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. - · Video Demonstrations allow playback of recorded sessions narrated by Instructors, walking through the steps of completing a given task in Maximo. In addition to the items available on the Training page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo. To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below. Continue reviewing this information until you are ready to start working in Maximo. IMPORTANT! Please DO NOT attempt to practice any of the steps in the Maximo Production system. If, after reviewing the materials, you are still uncomfortable with working in Maximo, contact your Maximo Site Lead for additional guidance.

Request Work VA/HTM Work Order Clerks can use the Maximo Service Requests application to create a new Service Request and the Work Order Tracking application to create new Work Orders. In some cases, only the Work Order will be created. Service Requests are used to request work to be done by another Department. - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the HTM Tech Training Materials page; under the HTM Work Order Clerk tab, select the Request Work User Guide to download the file. - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to the EAWM Maximo Video Demos. Under the section, Healthcare Technology Management (HTM) , locate the videos for the role VHA HTM WOC . The following video demonstrations pertain to this topic (please not

Under the section, Healthcare Technology Management (HTM) , locate the videos for the role VHA HTM WOC . The following video demonstrations pertain to this topic (please note that the videos will launch in a separate media player): - o Create a Service Request - o Create Related Work Order from Service Request - o Create a New Work Order without a Service Request - o Print Work Order ## 2. Plan and Approve Work and Execute Work VA Work Order Clerks use the Maximo Work Order Tracking application to plan and approve work orders. Work planning can be done on the Work Order Plans tab and a Job Plan can also be added to the work order if one is available for the tasks to be completed on the work order. - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the HTM Tech Training Materials page; under the HTM Work Order Clerk tab, select the Plan and Execute Work User Guide to download the file. - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to the EAWM Maximo

h Training Materials page; under the HTM Work Order Clerk tab, select the Plan and Execute Work User Guide to download the file. - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to the EAWM Maximo Video Demos. Under the section, Healthcare Technology Management (HTM) , locate the videos for the role VHA HTM WOC . The following video demonstrations pertain to this topic (please note that the videos will launch in a separate media player): - o Assign Ownership to a Responsible Shop-Tech - o Update Work Order Status-Approve Work Order ## 3. Asset Turn In Work Order An Asset Turn In Service Request processed a little differently than a typical Service Request. The key difference is that Classification of the Service Request is performed prior to creation of the Work Order. This ensures Sanitization and/or Decontamination of the Asset(s) is completed by the Responsible Tech. Depending on your local business process, it is verified by a supervisor, or, if authorized, a Tech can verify sa

itization and/or Decontamination of the Asset(s) is completed by the Responsible Tech. Depending on your local business process, it is verified by a supervisor, or, if authorized, a Tech can verify sanitization. Key points to remember after creating the Work Order from the Service Request, is to change the Status of the Service Request to WSAN (Waiting on Sanitization). Once the Work Order is completed by the Tech/Supervisor, the Service Request status of WSAN notifies the ISO to certify sanitization. ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the HTM Tech Training Materials page; under the HTM Work Order Clerk tab, select the Asset Turn In User Guide to download the file. - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to the EAWM Maximo Video Demos.
